The paper deals with compressed indexing, which is a problem in data structures and algorithms. The techniques used in the paper involve grammar construction and 2D-range reporting, which are commonly used in computational complexity and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents results on space complexity and query time, which are related to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
